The Downers Grove Golf Club is a unique and scenic course located minutes from I-88 and I-355. As a Certified Audubon Cooperative Sanctuary, this 9-hole course features mature trees, natural areas and wildflowers and offers enough elevation and water hazards to challenge every golfer. A driving range with 24 permanent and turf hitting stations, a large practice putting green, sand trap and chipping area. The range now features a covered shelter over 10 of the stations, which provide infrared heaters and ceiling fans for a comfortable golf experience even on rainy and cold days.

As a Certified Audubon Cooperative Sanctuary, this 9-hole course features mature trees, natural areas and wildflowers and offers enough elevation and water hazards to challenge every golfer. A driving range with 24 permanent and turf hitting stations, a large practice putting green, sand trap and chipping area. The range now features a covered shelter over 10 of the stations, which provide infrared heaters and ceiling fans for a comfortable golf experience even on rainy and cold days.

As a Certified Audubon Cooperative Sanctuary, this 9-hole course features mature trees, natural areas and wildflowers and offers enough elevation and water hazards to challenge every golfer. A driving range with 24 permanent and turf hitting stations, a large practice putting green, sand trap and chipping area. The range now features a covered shelter over 10 of the stations, which provide infrared heaters and ceiling fans for a comfortable golf experience even on rainy and cold days.
